text: I felt like such an asshole last night. Ppl finally encouraged me to play my nekusar deck after never letting me play it before. It was my first deck I made and haven’t played it since college, but had retouched it the night before

Turn 2 lightning greaves
Turn 3 phyrexian tyranny 
Turn 4 fate unraveler
Turn 5 nekusar - equip
Turn 6 windfall into winds of change
sometimes you just have the nut

Also played hazezon Tamar. A bunch of people got mana screwed, missing land drops.

Turn 3 chromatic lantern to give me red
Turn 4 shared animosity
Turn 5 Miraris wake
Turn 6 rampant growth and hazezon
Turn 7 created 7 1/1 tokens
“They don’t have haste right? Ok they’re fine”

Beast master ascension, Lovisa coldeyes, and mirror entity with 4 remaining mana to make them 12/12s that got +7/+0 on attack.
Oh I forgot the all important turn 2 grand abolisher. It was so on tempo and perfect
Grand Abolisher is such a good card
But it's almost always a bad sign when I see someone play one
We talked about that and Conqueror's Flail last night
I’ve only played Abolisher in my equipment deck rotations. Probably the fairest decks they play nice in.
It’s one of those cards that when it drops pretty often you can just expect staples.dec

text: Context, I’ve been throwing around a Naban Wizard tribal deck for a very long time, and well, it lacks wincons to say the least. There’s some tribal payoff with Super Delver of Secrets and other stuff, but I’m trying to figure out how the deck actually wins without being an absolute snore/pain to play against.
I mean, let's see if we can find a couple win-cons, then.
The impetus is I’m planning to build value-Emry, and figured I could try out Naban by making the two decks swappable.
So artifact based, then?
No, it’s just i can probably swap over some cards. Naban is its own entity.

I have stuff like Cloudstone.
It’s just hard to make it win (quickly) without soft-locking the table it feels like.
Yeah, I could see that.

There’s the +2/+1 Flying buff.
I’m sure there’s a few tribal equipment.
Diviner’s Wand maybe?
I was looking at combat, and there's some options there... it's just tough to rely on combat as a win without haste, is all.
That said, yeah, I would play Wand.
Islandwalk with [[Vedalken Plotter]] could also be some fun.
